.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-7-5::.
7 different games are played: mah-jongg, whist, billiard, monopoly, backgammon, canasta, poker
The people use 7 different means of transport: boat, subway, snowmobile, scooter, taxi, bus, trike
 1. the person playing billiard is on the right of the person playing backgammon##1
 2. the person driving the bus is somewhere between the person driving the boat and the person driving the snowmobile##7
 3. the person playing canasta is on the far left##1
 4. the person driving the scooter is not the person playing canasta##6
 5. the person driving the scooter is somewhere to the left of the person driving the boat##5
 6. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the person playing backgammon##5
 7. the person playing backgammon is somewhere to the left of the person playing billiard##5
 8. the person driving the boat is somewhere to the left of the person driving the trike##5
 9. the person driving the bus is not the person playing backgammon##6
10. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the person driving the scooter##5
11. the person playing backgammon is somewhere to the left of the person playing monopoly##5
12. the person playing billiard is the person driving the taxi##1
13. the person playing whist is on the right of the person playing canasta##1
14. the person playing whist is the person driving the subway##1
15. the person playing billiard is on the left of the person playing poker##1
16. the person playing monopoly is on the left of the person playing mah-jongg##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |      2      |     3     |    4    |   5    |    6    |   7    |
